The paper presents a method for unsupervised data analysis, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The method involves clustering, which is also a common topic in natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV). The regularizers used in the method enforce feature sharing/competition, which is related to feature selection and extraction, a topic in signal processing and information theory (cs.SI).
